{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-tipping-content-js","path":"/virgin_islands_(u.s.)","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"html":"<p>Tipping in the Virgin Islands is expected. In the USVI, tip as you would on the U.S. mainland. In restaurants, it is customary to leave at least 15 percent of the total bill, before any discounts or special reductions. Most servers at fast food or self-service restaurants do not require a tip, but when dining in a full service restaurant with a large group, remember that gratuities are almost never included (except for parties larger than 10).</p>\n<p>When checking baggage, tip the porter at least one dollar per bag. You should also tip maids, and depending on the level of service, it is polite to offer a gratuity to your concierge. If your hotel provides valet parking, it is advisable to tip the valet as well.</p>","frontmatter":{"path":"/virgin_islands_(u.s.)","title":"Virgin Islands (U.S.)","author":"Joni","date":"2019-11-22","image":"virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg"}},"image":{"childImageSharp":{"fluid":{"base64":"data:image/jpeg;base64,","aspectRatio":1.504,"src":"/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/90537/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg","srcSet":"/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/b3ebb/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 270w,\n/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/95b54/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 540w,\n/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/90537/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 1080w,\n/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/3cda3/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 1620w,\n/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/1f682/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 2160w,\n/static/b69eb56ca893a693b6a216f66929f915/7fcd2/virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg 3008w","sizes":"(max-width: 1080px) 100vw, 1080px"}}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"image":"virgin_islands_(u.s.).jpg"}}}